        [
          "An embraced scout, you used to follow a Brujah named Shepherd. He left, and you suspect he's in LA somewhere.",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Jenn Wolfe"
        ],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "Working with the US Calvary in Indian Territory had been more survival than anything. You were what they unflatteringly called a \"half-breed\" in the Army, a mixed race kid who no one trusted, but you could blend well and had pretty good tracking and scouting skills. That didn't stop them from looking at you as filth beneath their boot. One night, after too much to drink, some of the fine white boys from the east decided they would like to use you for sparring practice, for no reason other than you were half Indian. They beat the hell out of you, leaving you with your chest half caved in. They left you for dead. But a Nosferatu found you and taught you how to take your revenge. \n\nLike all the \"river rats\" in the sparse Midwest at the time, you took to hiding in places where humans gathered, towns along the river, where feeding was easiest. You became the monster, the boogey man they scared children with, ranging wide to find sustenance. It's where you honed your skill, especially silence. Angry at what you had become, you didn't particularly care. Others came along with the settlers, other vampires even. Shepherd was among them. He was a preacher, he claimed to have the word of his God and you found you were drawn to it. The anger and resentment you had felt since your turning melted in the assuredness of Shepherd's words. You came to believe in his good word, and became his apostle, his right hand as he ministered to other such damned creatures as yourself, bringing the word of God. You vowed to follow Shepherd wherever he went and to protect him as he followed God's mission.\n\nFor years, you roamed the Midwest, you serving as the scout to Shepherd to go ahead, ensure that all was safe, and warn him of what was ahead. On occasion, when it warranted, you worked for various princes as their spy and information gatherer as well, because it was lucrative to do so. You were on one such job for the Prince of Kansas City when Shepherd said he had to go. He'd been called to Los Angeles, the Lord was leading him there for reasons he didn't understand. Shepherd was always passionate about everything, and he left. You promised to follow as soon as your job was done, but, the Prince took forever and by the time you were able to follow Shepherd, he had disappeared. You aren't sure where he is, but you've tracked his trail to Los Angeles. With the sort of strange, religious things going on in this city, it's small wonder that Shepherd came here. Now you just have to find him."
        ],
